<aura:documentation>
    <aura:description>
        <p><code>ui:​panelManager</code>​ handles dialogs created by the <code>ui:panelDialog</code> component. 
          You only need one instance of <code>ui:​panelManager</code> in an app. 
        </p>
<pre>&lt;aura:component>    
    &lt;div class="container">
       &lt;ui:button press="{!c.showNonModal}" aura:id="detailTrigger" label="Show Non-Modal Dialog"/>
       &lt;ui:button press="{!c.showModal}" aura:id="forModal" label="Show Modal Dialog"/>
    &lt;/div>
    &lt;ui:panelManager />
&lt;/aura:component></pre>     
    <p>To customize the dialog body, create your own component and pass it in the <code>body</code> attribute, or create a component dynamically. Display the dialog by firing the <code>ui:openPanel</code> event and set its parameters. See <code>ui:panelDialog</code> for more information.</p>   
  </aura:description>
</aura:documentation>
